sources.title: Cjamango (1967) Western / Spaghetti Western | Full Movie
sources.description:
Just when Cjamango has won a bag of gold in a poker game, he is attacked by the gangs of El Tigre and Don Pablo. As he recovers from the injuries caused by the attack, Cjamango becomes attached to a Mexican boy, Manuel, and to a beautiful girl, Perla. El Tigre and Pablo are meanwhile at odds with one another about the gold, and Cjamango tries to play them against themselves. But there is also a mysterious stranger whose aims are unclear.

Director: Edoardo Mulargia
Writers: Vincenzo Musolino, Fabio Piccioni
Stars: Ivan Rassimov, Mickey Hargitay, Hélène Chanel
Genre: Western

Original title: Cjamango (1967) 

This film is available with English & Italian audio, & subtitles available in many language options.


00:00 Full Movie (with subtitles)
00:47 A tale of betrayal, revenge, and a search for justice unfolds in a Wild West setting.
16:05 A gunslinger named Cjamango seeks revenge and gold in a dangerous town.
28:15 A fast gunman named Cjamango gets involved in a plot to recover stolen gold and faces off against various adversaries.
46:10 A man named Cjamango is being pursued for gold and accused of murder, but claims he is innocent.
1:04:55 A Western-themed movie involving a search for gold, betrayal, and a final showdown.
